    • Method Detail

      • createTestMethods

        public static void createTestMethods(CodeElement codeElement,
                                     TestClass testClass)
        Creates TestMethods and TestAssertions for a given CodeElement and adds them to the given TestClass.
        Delegates the conversion of TestAssertions for the CodeElements properties to the PropertyAssertionConverter.
        Delegates the conversion of TestAssertions for the CodeElements super classes and interfaces to the RelationshipAssertionConverter.
        Delegates the conversion of TestAssertions for the CodeElements CodeTemplateParameters to the TemplateParameterAssertionConverter.
        Delegates the conversion of TestAssertions for the CodeElements CodeFields to the FieldAssertionConverter.
        Delegates the conversion of TestAssertions for the CodeElements CodeLiterals to the FieldAssertionConverter.
        Delegates the conversion of TestAssertions for the CodeElements CodeConstructors to the ConstructorAssertionConverter.
        Delegates the conversion of TestAssertions for the CodeElements CodeMethods to the MethodAssertionConverter.
        Parameters:
        codeElement - the CodeElement to create the TestAssertions for.
        testClass - the TestClass to which the created TestMethods should be added to.
